  "prompt": "What is Apple TV?",
  "response": "Apple TV is a digital media player and microconsole developed and sold by Apple Inc. It allows users to stream digital content from the iTunes Store, Netflix, Hulu, Amazon Prime Video, and other online services to their television. There are two main components:\n\n1. Apple TV Device\n- A small set-top box that connects to a television\n- Connects to the internet via Wi-Fi or Ethernet\n- Allows streaming of movies, TV shows, music, and other content\n- Supports apps and games\n- Comes in different generations with varying features\n\n2. Apple TV+ Streaming Service\n- A subscription-based streaming platform\n- Offers original TV shows, movies, and documentaries\n- Produced exclusively by Apple\n- Separate from the Apple TV device\n- Competes with services like Netflix and Disney+\n\nThe device enables users to:\n- Stream online content\n- Mirror content from Apple devices\n- Access the App Store\n- Play games\n- Use Siri for voice commands\n\nThere are different models available, with varying storage capacities and capabilities, including 4K resolution options.",
